            <div>
              <h2 id=3D"how-to-calculate-one-rep-max-without-a-calculator">=
How to calculate one rep max (without a calculator)</h2>
              <p>Calculating your one rep max (1RM), the maximum weight you=
 can lift for a single repetition, can be done using several methods. Howev=
er, it's safer and more common to estimate the 1RM using submaximal loads (=
lifting lighter weights for more reps) rather than testing it directly.</p>
              <p>Here's a widely-used formula to estimate 1RM:</p>
              <p>1RM =3D (Weight Lifted=C3=97Repetitions Performed / 30.48)=
 + Weight Lifted</p>
            </div>
